name: phosphatidate phosphatase
comment: This enzyme catalyses the Mg2+-dependent dephosphorylation of a 1,2-diacylglycerol-3-phosphate, yielding a 1,2-diacyl-sn-glycerol (DAG), the substrate for de novo lipid synthesis via the Kennedy pathway and for the synthesis of triacylglycerol. In lipid signalling, the enzyme generates a pool of DAG to be used for protein kinase C activation. The mammalian enzymes are known as lipins.

references.title: The enzymatic dephosphorylation of phosphatidic acids.
Phosphatidic acid phosphatase, a key enzyme in the regulation of lipid synthesis.
